\pard\f0\fs28    Plants from Portugal have sometimes been treated as subsp.{\b  meonantha} (Hoffmanns. & Link) R. Fernandes,{\i  Bol. Soc. Brot.} ser. 2, {\b 34}: 131 (1960), or as a distinct species, {\b A. occidentalis} Br.Bl., {\i Agron. Lusit. }{\b 18}: 89 (1956). They are densely villous with thick leaves, and the calyx has a narrow tube and narrow, acute teeth. These differences do not, however, seem to merit recognition at more than varietal rank.
