\pard\f0\fs28   {\b  A. rotundifolia} Willk. & Cutanda, {\i Linnaea }{\b 30}: 120 (1859), from mountain slopes of C. Spain, has stolons, spathulate lower leaves and lanceolate, acuminate calyx-lobes. It has sometimes been treated as a subspecies of {\b 3} but its status is not clear.
